Sequence Information.Peptide Name: AS-16 (synthetic AMPs, AS-21 analog, Lys-rich; XXA, UCLL1c)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (72.73%) toAS-21obtained by N-terminal sequence truncation of AS-21. K: 38%; R: 19%; I=L=F: 13%.Activity: active against E. coli ATCC 25922 or 4 clinical strains (MIC 8-16 ug/ml), P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853 or 4 clinical strrains (MIC 8-32 ug/ml) one at 128 ug/ml,  K. pneumoniae ATCC 13883 (MIC 32 ug/ml) or >128 ug/ml, A. baumannii (MIC 16 ug/ml), Gram+ S. aureus ATCC 29213 (MIC 8 ug/ml), MRSA (MIC 16 ug/ml), S. epidermidis (MIC 32 ug/ml), and C.albicans (MIC >128 ug/ml).
Literature Information.Author: Zhang M, Wang J, Li C, Wu S, Liu W, Zhou C, Ma L.2024
Literature Information.Title: Cathelicidin AS-12W Derived from the Alligator sinensis and Its Antimicrobial Activity Against Drug-Resistant Gram-Negative Bacteria In Vitro and In Vivo.
